*Prerequisites for Spin & Angular Momentum:*
- Spin-1/2 operators: Pauli matrices $sigma_x, sigma_y, sigma_z$. Eigenvalues are always plus.minus 1 regardless of the normal vector $n$.
- Measurement probabilities: $ P = |chevron.l +_n | +_m chevron.r|^2 = cos^2(theta/2) $, where $theta$ is the angle between SG axes.
- Addition of Angular Momentum: $J = J_1 + J_2$. Allowed values are $ |j_1 - j_2| <= j <= j_1 + j_2 $.
- Spin-Spin Interaction: $ J_1 dot J_2 = 1/2 (J^2 - J_1^2 - J_2^2) $.
